      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7, then take your<strong> chicken</strong> out of the fridge and open the packet to let it air</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into wedges, then add them to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
